						<div class="postbody">Ok I understand package cost was the same and still is the same between surface-mounted and through-hole components, and that PCB area cost is negligible, but then that still doesn't advocate through-hole components, it makes both choices legitimate.<br /><br />It's definitely bugging me that only a single UNROM PCB used a surface mounted SRAM.</div>

