					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm guessing some of the reason is the manufacturing infrastructure at the time. Most assembly lines were setup for through hole till the mid 90s and by then there was no point to switching over to a SMT design (re-design cost for a system reaching end-of-life). Re-tooling pick an place bots and moving from wave soldering to reflow ovens slowed the acceptance of SMT.<br />  OTOH, maybe Nintendo just wanted to keep things hacker friendly <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />Yogi</div>

